# Test with Changes

When you change code in vayeate-theme-studio, add or update tests that cover the change.

## Layer to Test File Mapping

| Layer | Test location |
|-------|----------------|
| State | `src/domain/state/*.test.ts` |
| Actions | `src/app/**/actions/*.test.ts` |
| Controllers | `src/domain/controllers/<controller>/<controller>.test.ts` (colocated in controller subdirectory) |
| Validations | `src/domain/validations/<validations>/<validator>.test.ts` (colocated next to each validator file) |
| Operations | `src/domain/operations/<operations>/<operations>.test.ts` (colocated in operation subdirectory) |
| Gateway/services | `src/gateway/services/*.test.ts` (when adding/changing services) |
| Gateway (theme/template/catalog/config/preview) | Colocated `*.test.ts` next to the gateway file |
| Viewmodel | `src/app/**/viewmodel/*.test.tsx` |
| UI (pages/components) | Colocated `*.test.tsx` next to the component |

## Guidelines

- Prefer testing public behavior and outcomes over implementation details
- Mock `window.electronAPI` in tests that trigger IPC calls (e.g. CREATE_CATALOG)
- Tests that use Node `fs` against a temp dir should add `@vitest-environment node`
- Before finishing, run `npm run test` in vayeate-theme-studio and fix any failures
